{"lemma":"طَلَقَ","slug":"طَلَقَ","root":"ط.ل.ق","root_slug":"ط-ل-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ل-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طَلَقَ","root":"طلق","pos":"V","occurrence_count":10},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26974","n26977","n26980"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to set loose; to free; to launch"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to release"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be divorced, to get divorced"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to divorce","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"talc, talcum","examples":[{"text":"طلق: محمد بن عبدون: حجر براق يتحلل إذا دق إلى طاقات صغار دقاق ويعمل منه مضاوىء للحمامات فيقوم مقام الزجاج ويسمى الفتخ والحسميا بالسريانية، وكوكب الأرض وعرق العروس. وقال الرازي في كتاب المدخل التعليمي الطلق: أنواع بحري ويمان وجبلي وهو يتصفح إذا دق صفائح بيض دقاق لها بصيص وبريق قال في كتاب علل المعادن: الطلق جنسان جنس يكون متصفحاً يتكون من حجارة الجص ويكون في جزيرة قبرص. ديسقوريدوس: الطلق هو حجر يكون بقبرص شبيه بالشب اليماني يتشظى وتتفسخ شظاياه فسخاً ويلقى ذلك الفسخ في النار ويلتهب ويخرج وهو متقد إلا أنه لا يحترق. الغافقي: هذا الجنس هو الجبسين وهو الطلق الأندلسي وقال علي بن محمد: الطلق ثلاثة أصناف يمان وهندي وأندلسي فاليمان أرفعها والأندلسي أوضعها والهندي متوسط بينهما فأما اليمان فهو صفائح دقاق أدق ما يكون مثل صفائح الفضة غير أن لونها لون الصدق والهندي مثل اليمان في شكله إلا أنه دونه في فعله والأندلسي يتصفح أيضاً غير أنه غليظ متجبس ويعرف بعرق العروس، وقال أرسطوطاليس وخاصيته أنه لو دقه الداق بالحديد والمطارق والهاون وكل شيء تدق به الأجسام لم تعمل فيه شيئاً وإن أمر عليه حجر الماس كسره من موضعه ثم تصيبه صحيحاً على ما وصفنا وليس يحتال له في حيلة لسحقه إلا بأن يجعل معه أحجار صغار ويجمع في مسح شعر أو ثوب خشن جداً ويحرك مع تلك الأحجار دائماً حتى يتحتت جسمه وتأكله شيئاً فشيئاً. قال علي بن محمد: حله يهون بأن يجعل في خرقة مع حصيات ويدخل في الماء الفاتر ثم يحرك برفق حتى ينحل ويخرج من الخرقة في الماء ثم يصفى عنه الماء ويترك في الشمس حتى يجف فيبقى في أسفل الإناء كالدقيق المطحون. قال الرازي: ويطلى بالطلق المواضع التي تدنى من الناركي لا تعمل النار فيها. ابن سينا: قال بعضهم في سقيه خطر لما فيه من تشبثه بشظايا المعدة وخملها وبالحلق والمريء وهو بارد في الأولى يابس في الثانية قابض حابس للدم وينفع من أورام الثديين والمذاكير وخلف الأذنين وسائر اللحم الرخو ابتداء ويحبس نفث الدم من الصدر بماء لسان الحمل ويحبس الدم من الرحم والمقعدة سقياً للمغسول منه بماء لسان الحمل وطلاء وينفع من دوسنطاريا. الغافقي: جيد للقروح التي تهيج بأطراف المجذومين ينقيها ويجبرها.","english":"De simplicibus medicinis opus magnum"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Persian تلک (talk)."},"ipa":["/tˤa.lu.qa/","/tˤal.la.qa/","/tˤalq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26974","headword_ar":"طَلْقٌ","root":"Tlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Loosed from his bond, set loose"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or], as expl. by IAar,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"let go;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaliyqN","text_ar":"طَلِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTolaqN","text_ar":"مُطْلَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having anything upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as expl. by Ks: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taloqu Alyadayoni","text_ar":"طَلْقُ اليَدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"a camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having the fore legs bound."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hubisa TaloqFA","text_ar":"حُبِسَ طَلْقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the CK,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalaqFA","text_ar":"طَلَقًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K accord. to the TA, [and this is agreeable with the preceding context in the K, but it requires confirmation which I do not find,]) and with damm, [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuloqFA","text_ar":"طُلْقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":",] accord. to the K, but correctly with two dammehs, [i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuluqFA","text_ar":"طُلُقًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (TA, and thus in the S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was imprisoned without shackle and without bond."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuluqN","text_ar":"طُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taloqu All~isaAni","text_ar":"طَلْقُ اللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taliyqu","text_ar":"طَلِيقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AllsAn","text_ar":"اللسان"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AllsAn","text_ar":"اللسان"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tiloqu","text_ar":"طِلْقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AllsAn","text_ar":"اللسان"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tulaqu","text_ar":"طُلَقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eloquent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste, in speech, and sweet therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~isaAni","text_ar":"اللِّسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munoTaliqu","text_ar":"مُنْطَلِقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaTal~iquhu","text_ar":"مُتَطَلِّقُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from impediment of the tongue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste in speech."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAnN TaloqN *aloqN","text_ar":"لِسَانٌ طَلْقٌ ذَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aliyqN","text_ar":"ذَلِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaliyqN","text_ar":"طَلِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uluqN","text_ar":"ذُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuluqN","text_ar":"طُلُقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ulaqN","text_ar":"ذُلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TulaqN","text_ar":"طُلَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) but the last two of these were unknown to As, and the latter of them was disallowed by IAar, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aliqN","text_ar":"ذَلِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaliqN","text_ar":"طَلِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) [expl. in the K as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tongue having sharpness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but correctly] meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tongue free from impediment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eloquent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chaste in speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw A@noTilaAqK","text_ar":"ذُو ا@نْطِلَاقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sharp."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taloqu Alyadayoni","text_ar":"طَلْقُ اليَدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alydyn","text_ar":"اليدين"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuluqu","text_ar":"طُلُقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alydyn","text_ar":"اليدين"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuloqu","text_ar":"طُلْقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alydyn","text_ar":"اليدين"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taliyqu","text_ar":"طَلِيقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Liberal, bountiful, munificent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K;) applied to a man: (S, Mgh, O, Msb:) and in like manner, a woman: (TA:) [or] a woman is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taloqapu Alyadayoni","text_ar":"طَلْقَةُ اليَدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and so, accord to AZ,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taloqu Alwajohi","text_ar":"طَلْقُ الوَجْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which [generally] has another meaning, expl. in what follows. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaduhu TaloqN","text_ar":"يَدُهُ طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His hand is liberal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bisoTN","text_ar":"بِسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bsT","text_ar":"بسط"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTolaqapN","text_ar":"مُطْلَقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S and K and TA in that art.:) or the latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opened;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maToluwqapN","text_ar":"مَطْلُوقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in the present art.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taloqu Alwajohi","text_ar":"طَلْقُ الوَجْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwjh","text_ar":"الوجه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tiloqu","text_ar":"طِلْقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuloqu","text_ar":"طُلْقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwjh","text_ar":"الوجه"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwjh","text_ar":"الوجه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taliqu","text_ar":"طَلِقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwjh","text_ar":"الوجه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taliyqu","text_ar":"طَلِيقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Laughing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"happy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerful, and bright, in the face,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"countenance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"happy, displaying openness and pleasantness, in the face;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone: (Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwjh","text_ar":"الوجه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taliyqu","text_ar":"طَلِيقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"open and pleasant, and goodly, in countenance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaliyqN","text_ar":"طَلِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joyful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"open"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheer-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1873},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ful, in countenance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [And it is there said that the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqaAt","text_ar":"طَلْقَات"},{"kind":"text","text":": but this is app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuloqaAnN","text_ar":"طُلْقَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiloqaAnN","text_ar":"طِلْقَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwojuhN","text_ar":"اُوْجُهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAliqu","text_ar":"طَوَالِقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not allowable, except in poetry. (IAar, TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN TaloqN","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, S, Mgh, O, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN TaloqapN","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ طَلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, Mgh, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, Msb, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a night, in which is neither heat nor cold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh, O, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is no cold nor anything hurtful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is no rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is no wind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the cold is mild:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA: [after which is added,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn AyAm TaloqAt","text_ar":"من ايام طَلْقات"},{"kind":"text","text":": but the last word seems, as in an instance before mentioned, to be mistranscribed, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AyAm","text_ar":"ايام"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay~aAm","text_ar":"اَيَّام"},{"kind":"text","text":") may be a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layaAlK","text_ar":"لَيَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN TaloqN","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a night in which is no cold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the wind is still:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN TaloqapN","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ طَلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a moon-lit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bright, night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, O, TA:) and one says also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN TaAliqapN","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ طَالِقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a still,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bright, night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layaAlK TawaAliqu","text_ar":"لَيَالٍ طَوَالِقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant nights in which is neither heat nor cold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Er-Rá'ee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"falam~aA Ealatohu Al$~amosu fiY yawomi TaloqapK"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomi layolapK TaloqapK","text_ar":"يَوْمِ لَيْلَةٍ طَلْقَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And when the sun came upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a day of a night in which was neither cold nor wind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., in a day after such a night; for the Arabs commence with the night, before the day: and the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY yawomi TaloqapK","text_ar":"فِى يَوْمِ طَلْقَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in like manner in a verse of Dhu-r-Rummeh. (Az, TA.) ―         -b6-  For the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taloqu Alyadi","text_ar":"طَلْقُ اليَدِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlyumonaY","text_ar":"اليُمْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (applied to a horse, accord. to the K,) see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuluqN","text_ar":"طُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b7-  And for other meanings assigned in the K to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuluqN","text_ar":"طُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pain of childbirth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarabahaA AlT~aloqu","text_ar":"ضَرَبَهَا الطَّلْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pain of childbirth smote her"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuliqat","text_ar":"طُلِقَت"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is the inf. n.]       -A3-  And [it is said to signify]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sort of medicine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalaqN","text_ar":"طَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half, in two places."}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","O","Msb","Mgh","L","IAar","AZ","Lth","AA","IDrd"]},{"entry_id":"n26977","headword_ar":"طَلَقٌ","root":"Tlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", second sentence. ―         -b2-  Also the subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talaqati AlA_ibilu","text_ar":"طَلَقَتِ الاـِبِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AZ, S, TA: [see 1, second sentence:]) and [as such] signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeying"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of camels]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during the night to arrive at the water in the next night, there being two nights between them and the water; the first of which nights is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~alaqu","text_ar":"الطَّلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapu AlT~alaqi","text_ar":"لَيْلَةُ الطَّلَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawozN","text_ar":"حَوْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pastor loosing them to repair to the water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yajolibuhA","text_ar":"يَجْلِبُها"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuxal~iyhaA","text_ar":"يُخَلِّيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and leaving them to pasture while going thither: the camels after the driving, during the first night, are said to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAliqu","text_ar":"طَوَالِقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in the second night,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawaAribu","text_ar":"قَوَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~alaqu","text_ar":"الطَّلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the first of two days intervening between the camels and the water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqarabu","text_ar":"القَرَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the second: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapu","text_ar":"لَيْلَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~alaqi","text_ar":"الطَّلَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the night in which the faces of the camels are turned towards the water and during which they are left to pasture;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapu Alqarabi","text_ar":"لَيْلَةُ القَرَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the second night: (As, TA:) but it has been said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapu AlT~alaqi","text_ar":"لَيْلَةُ الطَّلَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the second of the nights in which the camels repair to the water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"Th says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~alaqu","text_ar":"الطَّلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the second of two days during which the camels seek the water when it is two days distant from them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqarabu","text_ar":"القَرَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the first of those days: and it is said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapu AlT~alaqi","text_ar":"لَيْلَةُ الطَّلَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the night of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the turning of the faces of the camels towards the water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this explanation was not pleasing to ISd. (TA.) [See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawozN","text_ar":"حَوْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which it is used tropically.] ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A heat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single run,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"run at once, to a goal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awoTN","text_ar":"شَوْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, IAth, O, Msb, K, TA;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a running,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without restraining himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without stopping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a goal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utmost extent to which a horse runs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says of a horse,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA TalaqFA","text_ar":"عَدَا طَلَقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talaqayoni","text_ar":"طَلَقَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ran a heat"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two heats"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, Msb, K. [In the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqFA","text_ar":"طَلْقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taloqayoni","text_ar":"طَلْقَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  And (hence, TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A share,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, A, O, K, TA,) of property [&c.]. (A, TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A shackle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pair of shackles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayodN","text_ar":"قَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of skins:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rope strongly twisted, so that it will stand up."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTolaAqN","text_ar":"اَطْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"which signifies The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intestines into which the food passes from the stomach, termed the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoEaA='","text_ar":"اَمْعَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqotaAb","text_ar":"اَقْتَاب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the belly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, O, K; * [in some copies of the last of which,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqunobu","text_ar":"القُنْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqitobu","text_ar":"القِتْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as one of the words explaining"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~alaqu","text_ar":"الطَّلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) so in one or more of the dialects: AO says, in the belly are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTolaAq","text_ar":"اَطْلَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalaqN","text_ar":"طَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, TA;) meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streaks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaraAy^iq","text_ar":"طَرَايِق"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the belly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talaqu AlbaToni","text_ar":"طَلَقُ البَطْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also expl. [in like manner] as meaning the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~ap","text_ar":"جُدَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the belly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above. (TA.)       -A3-  Also The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uborum","text_ar":"شُبْرُم"},{"kind":"text","text":": [but what plant is meant by this is doubtful:] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plant that is used in dyes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or this is a mistake: (K:) [or] accord. to Ibn-'Abbád, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aloqu","text_ar":"الطَّلْقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is used in dyes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uborum","text_ar":"شُبْرُم"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, TA: *) and (K) accord. to As, (O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalaqN","text_ar":"طَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of medicament,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which, when one is anointed therewith,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the extract thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prevents the burning of fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of plant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says As: (O:) the appellation by which it is generally known is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taloq","text_ar":"طَلْق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent; (O, K;) or this pronunciation is incorrect: (K:) and AHát mentions, (K, TA,) on the authority of As, (TA,) its being termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiloqN","text_ar":"طِلْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but it is not a plant: it is of the nature of stones, and of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what are termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lixaAf","text_ar":"لِخَاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thin white stones]; and probably he [referring to As] heard that it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kawokabu AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"كَوْكَبُ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and therefore supposed it to be a plant; for if it were a plant, fire would burn it; but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fire does not burn it, unless by means of artful contrivances:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) the word is arabicized, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talako","text_ar":"تَلَكْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA: in the O written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tilk","text_ar":"تِلك"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [it is the well-known mineral termed"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talc:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the Ra-ees [Ibn-Seenà, whom we call “ Avicenna, ”] says, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is a brightlyshining stone, that separates, when it is bruised, into several laminæ and split pieces, of which are made"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaAwiY","text_ar":"مَضَاوِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaAwiy^","text_ar":"مَضَاوِي"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small circular panes which are inserted in apertures to admit light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cupolas of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hot baths, instead of glass: the best is that of El-Yemen; then that of India; then that of El-Undulus"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"El-Andalus"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the art employed in dissolving it consists in putting it into a piece of rag with some pebbles and immersing it in tepid water, then moving it about gently until it becomes dissolved and comes forth from the piece of rag into the water, whereupon the water is strained from it, and it is put in the sun to dry. (K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA","As","Msb","M"]},{"entry_id":"n26980","headword_ar":"طُلُقٌ","root":"Tlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, TA,) with two dammehs, (Msb, TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) but this requires consideration, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Not shackled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a she-camel, (S, O, Msb, TA,) and to a he-camel, (S, O, TA,) and to a person imprisoned; (O, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqN","text_ar":"طَالِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a she-camel; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuluqN","text_ar":"طُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more common: (Aboo-Nasr, TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuluqN","text_ar":"طُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTolaAqN","text_ar":"اَطْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", second sentence. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAnN TuluqN *uluqN","text_ar":"لِسَانٌ طُلُقٌ ذُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b3-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuluqu Alyadayon","text_ar":"طُلُقُ اليَدَيْن"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"again. ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuluqu","text_ar":"طُلُقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHodaY AalqawaAy^imi","text_ar":"اـِحْدَى اَلقَوَايِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having one of the legs without"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the whiteness termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aHojiyl","text_ar":"التَّحْجِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuluqu Alyadi AlyumonaY","text_ar":"طُلُقُ اليَدِ اليُمْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyd AlymnY","text_ar":"اليد اليمنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuloqu","text_ar":"طُلْقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, [in this case again deviating from other authorities,]) (tropical:)  A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHojiyl","text_ar":"تَحْجِيل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the right fore leg;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyd AlymnY","text_ar":"اليد اليمنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTolaqu","text_ar":"مُطْلَقُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyadayoni","text_ar":"اليَدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTolaqa","text_ar":"مُطْلَقَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the fore legs free from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHjyl","text_ar":"تحجيل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1874},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b5-  [As an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuluqN","text_ar":"طُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ibn-' Abbád, O,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, [but this, as in the instances above, is questionable,]) signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A gazelle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-' Abbád, O, K:) so called because of the quickness of its running: (O, * TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTolaAqN","text_ar":"اَطْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-'Abbád, O, K.) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dog of the chase:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) because he is let loose; or because of the quickness of his running at the chase: (TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTolaAqN","text_ar":"اَطْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is mentioned by Ibn-' Abbád as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dogs of the chase."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","TA","K"]}]}}